>>John wrote: I almost always see oil on plug wires as a consequence of
overpressure in the crankcase blowing out the vent system. Doesn't
quite match your description, but it's easy to misjudge the direction
of travel sometimes.<<

If it is crankcase blow by, make sure to check that the valve cover
seals are sealed.  If not the engine can build up pressure and blow out
lots of oil.
